Install Mysql and Redis for rails development. This repo use the new ChefDk package that contains:

- Chef
- Berkshelf 3.0
- Test Kitchen
- ChefSpec
- Foodcritic

install
=======
Download and install VirtualBox from https://www.virtualbox.org/wiki/Downloads
Download and install chefdk from https://downloads.chef.io/chef-dk/
Download and install vagrant package from https://www.vagrantup.com/downloads.html

git clone git@github.com:jospergon/rails_development_vagrant_machine.git
cd rails_development_vagrant_machine
bundle install


vagrant up


In the rails project add the follows lines n the file config/database.yml

base: &base
  adapter: mysql2
  encoding: utf8
  pool: 5
  username: root
  password: "1234"
  host: localhost

development:
  database: healthyfoodnow_dev
  <<: *base

test:
  database: healthyfoodnow_test
  <<: *base
